  "text": "The Kafka producer TimeoutException with message 'Expiring N record(s) for topic-partition' is triggered by the following components:\n\n1. **TimeoutException Class Definition** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/errors/TimeoutException.java): The TimeoutException class is defined at line 22 as a public class extending RetriableException. This is the exception type thrown when producer records expire due to timeout.\n\n2. **delivery.timeout.ms Configuration Constant** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/ProducerConfig.java): At line 165, the configuration constant DELIVERY_TIMEOUT_MS_CONFIG = \"delivery.timeout.ms\" is defined. This parameter is documented at lines 166-173 as an upper bound on the time to report success or failure after a send() call returns.\n\n3. **Record Batch Expiration Logic - RecordAccumulator.expiredBatches()** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/RecordAccumulator.java): The expiredBatches() method at line 465 is responsible for identifying batches that have exceeded the delivery timeout. It iterates through all producer batches and checks if each batch.hasReachedDeliveryTimeout(deliveryTimeoutMs, now) at line 473. Expired batches are collected in the expiredBatches list.\n\n4. **Error Generation - Sender.runOnce()** (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/Sender.java): The runOnce() method at lines 404-423 orchestrates the expiration process. It calls accumulator.expiredBatches(now) at line 407, then iterates through each expired batch (line 415). At lines 416-417, it constructs the error message \"Expiring \" + recordCount + \" record(s) for \" + topicPartition + \":\" + (elapsed time) + \" ms has passed since batch creation\". Finally, at line 418, it creates and throws a TimeoutException with this message via failBatch().\n\nThe flow is: Sender.runOnce() → calls accumulator.expiredBatches() → which checks hasReachedDeliveryTimeout() for each batch → returns expired batches → Sender creates TimeoutException with 'Expiring N record(s)' message."
}

